    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.03758.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date>10 AM <hi rend="underline">Monday</hi></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My Dear Walt</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>If it were not so hot I w'd come down this morning. I send you "Tobe Hodge" (McIlvains)<ptr target="loc.03758_n1"/> letter.<ptr target="loc.03758_n5"/> 
                He is a very bright fellow: one of <hi rend="underline">us "true fellows</hi> of the upper Rhine."<ptr target="loc.03758_n3"/></p>
            <p>We must go see him at his little country box and "inspect" his <hi rend="underline">decanter</hi>!</p>
            <p>I send the "Power Temperance" sketch &amp; the letter. You will like the story. Don't lose them</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Yr Friend:</salute>
                <signed>James M Scovel<ptr target="loc.03758_n4"/></signed>
                <address>
                    <addrLine>To W.W. Esq.</addrLine>
                </address>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.03758.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
            <note type="editorial" resp="#ww" place="right">Scovel</note>       
        </body>
    </text>
